@@eThe Cinderteeth -- Prism Archive, Founding Record@@N

When the founders of Kiess broke ground on Evermeet's ruins, they
found an @@dobsidian disc@@N in the collapsed civic hall bearing the
triune seal of the @@WSpirebound Conclave@@N: Ember, Prism, Pale. That
disc proved Evermeet had signed @@rsealed warrants@@N transferring its
own citizens to the Conclave's custody. The Cinderteeth Mountains
are not distant geology to Kiess. They are the @@rorigin point@@N of
the abuse that wrote our founding charter.

The @@WConclave@@N built their sanctum in the Western Fold precisely
because isolation made accountability impossible. They embedded
@@lresonance crystals@@N throughout the Bellspine ridge, instruments
no one could audit. When they collapsed, those anchors were never
retrieved. This is @@rsealed-warrant thinking@@N writ in stone: an
authority that installs infrastructure, extracts compliance, and
then vanishes, leaving the consequences for others to manage.

The @@yTrade Syndics@@N track the Cinderteeth for a more immediate
reason: seismic risk to western routes. The mountains are coupled
to deep continental faults. Tremors propagate unpredictably. The
@@rAshfall catastrophe@@N sent volcanic clouds across the continent,
poisoned wells as far as the Great Northern Forest, and devastated
Kowloon's delta. Convoy marshals along Roc Road carry @@yHazard
Doctrine@@N protocols copied from the Cinderteeth route houses --
the @@WSilent Bell Protocol@@N for resonance shifts, @@rdouble-water
doctrine@@N against contamination. These are not superstitions.
They are law written in the names of the dead.

@@dWall Command@@N notes that the @@WChalkwind Saddles@@N remain the only
viable commercial transit through the range. The @@yGlasswash Fans@@N
produce obsidian and sulfur that eastern markets prize. But every
trade route through the Cinderteeth passes near Conclave ruins,
and every ruin still hums with crystal residue that no living
authority maintains or monitors.

The @@rAsh Cult@@N claims eruptions are divine verdicts against civic
corruption -- a degraded echo of the @@yVentspeaker@@N tradition,
stripped of its empirical discipline and loaded with apocalyptic
certainty. The Syndics classify them as a route hazard, not a
theological concern.

@@yThe Prism teaches@@N: the Conclave did not fall because its research
was flawed. It fell because it operated beyond oversight. Kiess
exists because Evermeet trusted a sealed disc from an unaccountable
mountain authority, and paid for that trust in lives. We do not
repeat that transaction.
